### What This Does NOT Change (Intentionally)

- **No inline style overrides** -- bgColor, borderColor, borderWidth, borderStyle, borderRadius, color, fontFamily remain fully user-controlled.
- **No JS/JSX changes** -- everything is pure CSS.
- **No new CSS classes requiring JSX edits** -- all enhancements use existing selectors or pseudo-elements.
- **No `!important` usage** -- inline styles from JS naturally win in specificity, which is what we want.
- **No changes to NoteStyleEditor, InlineNoteEditor, or ReadOnlyNoteView components.**
- **No changes to the `.note-inner-container` system** -- those inner containers have their own styling system.

